---

<SiteLayout
  site="28grams"
  canonical="https://28grams.vip/best-instant-pot-recipes"
  schema={schema}
>
  <style>
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; background: #0a060a; color: #e0d0d8; min-height: 100vh; }
code, .mono { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

:root {
  --card-bg: #120c10;
  --border-color: #2a1820;
  --accent-color: #C2185B;
  --text-secondary: #888;
}

.hero { text-align: center; padding: 48px 24px 24px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a0a14 0%, #0a060a 100%); }
.hero h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; font-weight: 900; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.hero h1 span { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-color), #ff6b9d); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
.hero p { color: #666; font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; }
.main { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 20px 40px; }

/* Chart Card */
.chart-card {
  background: var(--card-bg);
  border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
  border-radius: 16px;
  overflow: hidden;
  margin-bottom: 32px;
}
.chart-header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 16px 20px;
  background: #150d12;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}
.chart-header h2 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; }

/* Table Container */
.table-container {
  width: 100%;
  overflow-x: auto;
}
.compare-table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  min-width: 800px;
}
.compare-table th {
  text-align: left;
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  background: #1a1015;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color);
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
}
.compare-table td {
  padding: 12px 16px;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #c8b8c0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1015;
}
.compare-table tr:hover td { background: #1a1015; }
.compare-table td:first-child { font-weight: 600; color: #fff; }

.recipe-name { font-weight: bold; color: #fff; }

/* SEO content */
.content { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px; }
.content h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 40px 0 14px; }
.content h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
.content h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: #ddd; margin: 24px 0 10px; }
.content p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #777; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.content ul, .content ol { padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.content li { font-size: 0.88rem; color: #777; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 4px; }
.content strong { color: #ccc; }

/* Recipe Details */
.recipe-section { margin-bottom: 40px; padding-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
.recipe-section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
.recipe-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.recipe-header h3 { margin: 0; font-size: 1.3rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
.recipe-meta { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); background: #1a1015; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }

/* FAQ */
.faq-list { margin-top: 24px; }
.faq-item { margin-bottom: 24px; }
.faq-q { font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
.faq-a { color: #777; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .hero h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  .recipe-header { flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
}
  </style>

<div class="hero">
  <h1>Best Instant Pot Recipes <span>Guide</span> 🥘</h1>
  <p>25 ultimate Instant Pot recipes organized by category. Master pressure cooking with our pro tips, button guide, and conversion charts.</p>
</div>

<div class="main">

  <div class="chart-card">
    <div class="chart-header">
      <h2>25 Best Instant Pot Recipes by Category</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Rank</th>
            <th>Recipe</th>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Cook Time</th>
            <th>Pressure</th>
            <th>Release</th>
            <th>Serves</th>
            <th>Difficulty</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {recipes.map((recipe, index) => (
            <tr>
              <td>{index + 1}</td>
              <td class="recipe-name">{recipe.name}</td>
              <td>{recipe.category}</td>
              <td class="mono">{recipe.cookTime}</td>
              <td>{recipe.pressure}</td>
              <td>{recipe.release}</td>
              <td>{recipe.serves}</td>
              <td>{recipe.difficulty}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<div class="content">
  <h2>Instant Pot Button Guide</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pressure Cook (or Manual):</strong> The most used button. Cooks food at High or Low pressure for a set time.</li>
    <li><strong>Sauté:</strong> Acts like a skillet. Used to brown meats, sauté vegetables before pressure cooking, or simmer/thicken sauces after cooking.</li>
    <li><strong>Keep Warm / Cancel:</strong> Press once to cancel any current program. The Keep Warm function automatically turns on after pressure cooking ends.</li>
    <li><strong>Slow Cook:</strong> Replicates a traditional slow cooker. Usually requires adjusting settings (Less, Normal, More) to match Low or High slow cooker settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Yogurt:</strong> A low-heat function to pasteurize milk and ferment yogurt. Does not use pressure.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Slow Cooker to Pressure Cooker Conversion Chart</h2>
  <div class="chart-card" style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <div class="table-container">
      <table class="compare-table" style="min-width: 100%;">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Slow Cooker Time (Low)</th>
            <th>Slow Cooker Time (High)</th>
            <th>Instant Pot Time (High Pressure)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>8 hours</td>
            <td>4 hours</td>
            <td>25-30 minutes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>6 hours</td>
            <td>3 hours</td>
            <td>15-20 minutes</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>4 hours</td>
            <td>2 hours</td>
            <td>10-15 minutes</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p><em>Note: Add 10-15 minutes to Instant Pot times to account for the time it takes to build pressure. Always use at least 1 cup of liquid when pressure cooking.</em></p>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    {schema[1].mainEntity.map((faq: any) => (
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">{faq.name}</div>
        <div class="faq-a">{faq.acceptedAnswer.text}</div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
</SiteLayout>